activity_scotland_rates_2018 <- activity_hb %>%
    filter(hb_name == "Scotland"
           & !age_group %in% c("under75 years") 
           & sex != "All"
           & diagnosis == "Stroke"
           & admission_type == "All"
           & year == 2018
         ) %>% 
  select(age_group, sex, crude_rate, easr) %>% 
  rename(crude_rate_act = crude_rate,
         easr_act = easr) 
activity_scotland_discharges <- activity_hb %>%
    filter(hb_name == "Scotland"
           & !age_group %in% c("under75 years") 
           & sex != "All"
           & diagnosis == "Stroke"
           & admission_type == "All"
         ) %>% 
  select(year, age_group, sex, number_of_discharges)
mortality_scotland_rates_2018 <- mortality_hb %>% 
  filter(hb_name == "Scotland" 
           & !age_group %in% c("under75 years") 
           & sex != "All"
           & diagnosis == "Stroke"
           & year == 2018) %>% 
  select(age_group, sex, crude_rate, easr) %>% 
  rename(crude_rate_mort = crude_rate,
         easr_mort = easr)
mortality_scotland_deaths <- mortality_hb %>% 
  filter(hb_name == "Scotland" 
           & !age_group %in% c("under75 years") 
           & sex != "All"
           & diagnosis == "Stroke") %>% 
  select(year, age_group, sex, number_of_deaths)
population_scotland <- population_ages %>% 
  filter(hb_name == "Scotland" & sex != "All" & year >= 2009) %>% 
  group_by(year, sex, age_band2) %>% 
  summarise(population = sum(count))
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'year', 'sex'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
population_scotland <- population_scotland %>% 
  left_join(mortality_scotland_rates_2018,
            by = c("sex", 
                   "age_band2" = "age_group")) %>% 
  left_join(activity_scotland_rates_2018,
            by = c("sex", 
                   "age_band2" = "age_group"))
population_scotland <- population_scotland %>% 
  left_join(mortality_scotland_deaths,
            by = c("year", "sex", 
                   "age_band2" = "age_group")) %>% 
  left_join(activity_scotland_discharges,
            by = c("year", "sex", 
                   "age_band2" = "age_group"))
population_scotland <- population_scotland %>% 
  mutate(
    deaths_forecast = if_else(year <= 2018,
                              number_of_deaths,
                              population/100000 * easr_mort),
    cases_forecast = if_else(year <= 2018,
                             number_of_discharges,
                             population/100000 * easr_act),
    type = if_else(year <= 2018, 
                   "actual",
                   "projection")
  )
population_scotland %>%
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = year,
      y = deaths_forecast,
      colour = type) +
  geom_line() +
  facet_grid(age_band2 ~ sex, scales = "free")
